# B4 Performance Tuning (Phase 2)

The initial EfficientNet-B4 training showed a regression in robustness to Noise (89% vs 92% previously) and a relatively low training accuracy (~89%), suggesting the model is over-regularized and struggling to learn the underlying features behind the high-intensity noise.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Over-Regularization Fix**: We are reducing the total dropout and stochastic depth to allow the model more capacity to learn.
> **Gradient Accumulation**: To stabilize training with `BATCH_SIZE=8`, we will accumulate gradients for 4 steps (effective batch size = 32).
> **Softened Noise**: The Gaussian noise being added to training was `std=0.1`, which is too high for natural MRI patterns. We are reducing this to `0.03`.

## Proposed Changes

### [main.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/main.py)

- **Regularization**:
    - Update [HybridModel](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval.py#137-153) to use `drop_rate=0.2` (was 0.4) and `drop_path_rate=0.1` (was 0.2).
    - Change classifier `Dropout` to `0.3` (was 0.5).
- **Augmentation Tuning**:
    - Reduce second [AddGaussianNoise](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/main.py#205-217) `std` to `0.03` (was 0.1).
    - Reduce `GaussianBlur` `sigma` range to [(0.1, 1.0)](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval_clean_noisy_model.py#138-222).
- **Optimization**:
    - Add `GRADIENT_ACCUMULATION_STEPS = 4`.
    - Set `LEARNING_RATE = 5e-4` (more conservative for B4).
    - Update the training loop to track and step the optimizer/scheduler only every N steps.

### [eval.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval.py)
- Update [HybridModel](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval.py#137-153) classifier dropout to `0.3` to match the new tuning.

